The paper deals with the design of neural network architectures using automated methods, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep learning in various domains, as mentioned in the abstract, suggests that the paper could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on feedforward architectures and the use of probability matrices to represent network structures suggest that computer vision (cs.CV) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) could also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the use of an estimation of distribution algorithm in the architecture search algorithm suggests that the paper could also be classified under systems and control (cs.SY).
